<p>Two buses and two other vehicles collided in the early hours of Wednesday on the busy Kampala‑Gulu highway in Kiryandongo district, killing 46 people and leaving others injured, police and local reports said; authorities initially reported a higher toll before hospital counts were revised [aljazeera.com#1][straitstimes.com#1][dw.com#1][scmp.com#1][rt.com#1][bbc.com#1]. Police said the crash happened just after midnight when overtaking manoeuvres caused a head‑on collision and a subsequent chain reaction that overturned multiple vehicles, and emergency teams moved the injured to Kiryandongo hospital and nearby facilities [scmp.com#1][aljazeera.com#1][rt.com#1]. Local officials are conducting post‑mortems and identification at Kiryandongo hospital while urging motorists to exercise greater caution on the highway [rt.com#1][aljazeera.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/QQPhpTyvSWqcyjpdQyxjhPruvXFyc26TfBZTLypSzziCirBWLYhtf1pZKv4ygO48TnvQpVliiKYjbfAhkdzZcpXpCSryJgL8yO9IBhQpZ9DkzijnQQ-wGMlxuHQKP3Giz8AJsgDXLk-HpxZHrREZljuWTZ3QrFJ9t3S7T8rJKA' alt='Rescue personnel and bystanders at the scene of the multi‑vehicle crash on the Kampala‑Gulu highway' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Cause reported: Police said the crash stemmed from simultaneous overtaking attempts that led to a head‑on collision and a chain reaction overturning several vehicles, according to multiple reports [aljazeera.com#1][arabnews.com#1][rt.com#1].</li><li>Emergency handling: Rescue teams transported the injured to Kiryandongo hospital and other nearby facilities, and the deceased were taken to the same hospital for post‑mortems and identification [rt.com#1][aljazeera.com#1].</li><li>Reporting corrections: Authorities first reported a higher death toll before publicly revising the figure after hospital verification, prompting updated counts from police and medical staff [straitstimes.com#1][aljazeera.com#1].</li><li>Road safety context: The Kampala‑Gulu route is one of Uganda’s busiest and the country frequently records fatal bus and truck crashes along poorly maintained roads, according to regional coverage [scmp.com#1][dw.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>We confirm that the total number of fatalities resulting from the tragic fatal crash along the Kampala‑Gulu Highway at Kitaleeba Village stands at 46, according to the latest update from the hospital - Uganda police</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Uganda police: Police described the collision as a result of overtaking manoeuvres that produced a head‑on impact and a chain reaction, and they provided updated casualty figures after hospital verification. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/22/bus-collision-on-highway-near-ugandas-capital-kampala-kills-63-people'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li><li>Local hospital and emergency teams: Medical teams received the injured at Kiryandongo hospital, and the facility is conducting post‑mortems and identification of the deceased. (<a href='https://www.rt.com/africa/626805-uganda-buses-collide-on-highway/'>RT</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/22/bus-collision-on-highway-near-ugandas-capital-kampala-kills-63-people'>Collision involving multiple vehicles on Uganda highway kills 46 people</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/Ugandan-police-lower-death-toll-from-major-bus-crash-to-46'>Ugandan police lower death toll from major bus crash to 46</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/uganda-dozens-killed-in-highway-bus-collision/a-74452693'>Uganda: Dozens killed in highway bus collision</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/africa/article/3329925/buses-collide-head-uganda-killing-least-46'>‘Head-on’ bus collision kills at least 46 in Uganda</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://allafrica.com/stories/202510220065.html'>Uganda: 63 Dead in Horrific Kampala-Gulu Highway Crash</a> - allafrica.com</li><li><a href='https://www.cbsnews